Package fr.sorbonne_u.cps.replication.interfaces

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CombinatorI<T>
    The functional interface CombinatorI declares the method to be implemented by a combinator class or represented by a lambda expression.
    NotificationsCI
    The component interface NotificationsCI declares the method used to notify a dispatcehr about the current state of a server.
    NotificationsCI.StateI
    The interface StateI must be implemented by the class used to represent the current state of a server.
    PortFactoryI
    The interface PortFactoryI declares a set of signatures to be implemented by a port factory.
    ReplicableCI<T>
    The component interface ReplicableCI declares the signature of the service that will be proposed as replicated service.
    ReplicaI<T>
    The interface ReplicaI declares the signature of the service implementation that will be proposed as replicated service.
    SelectorI
    The functional interface SelectorI declares the method to be implemented by a selector class or represented by a lambda expression.
